title: Tassel, 17th century
medium:
Medium: linen
Technique: braided and knotted
creditline: Bequest of Richard Cranch Greenleaf in memory of his mother, Adeline Emma Greenleaf
description: Tiny tassel of linen, braided and knotted. Double loops attached to short stem terminating in small round ball which is entirely covered with clusters made of small knots.
